<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>{{senderName}} shared Memory access with you</title>
  <style>
    body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif; background: #f5f5f5; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    .container { max-width: 620px; margin: 40px auto; background: #fff; border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08); }
    .header { background: #1a1a2e; padding: 32px 40px; }
    .header h1 { color: #fff; margin: 0; font-size: 22px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.3px; }
    .header p { color: #9ca3af; margin: 6px 0 0; font-size: 14px; }
    .body { padding: 32px 40px; color: #333; }
    .body p { line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 16px; font-size: 15px; }
    .what-is { background: #f0f4ff; border-left: 3px solid #4f6ef7; border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0; padding: 16px 20px; margin: 20px 0 24px; }
    .what-is p { margin: 0; font-size: 14px; color: #374151; }
    .key-box { background: #fff8e1; border: 1px solid #ffe082; border-radius: 6px; padding: 18px 22px; margin: 24px 0; }
    .key-box .label { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.6px; color: #92400e; margin: 0 0 8px; }
    .key-box .warning { font-size: 12px; color: #b45309; margin: 10px 0 0; }
    .code { font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; background: #1e293b; color: #e2e8f0; padding: 10px 14px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 13px; display: block; margin: 6px 0; overflow-x: auto; white-space: pre; white-space: pre-wrap; word-break: break-all; }
    .key-box .code { background: #37474f; }
    .section { margin: 28px 0; }
    .section h2 { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; color: #111; margin: 0 0 6px; }
    .section .subtitle { font-size: 13px; color: #6b7280; margin: 0 0 14px; }
    .client { background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 6px; padding: 18px 22px; margin: 12px 0; }
    .client h3 { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: #1a1a2e; margin: 0 0 4px; }
    .client .path { font-size: 12px; color: #6b7280; margin: 0 0 10px; font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; }
    .scopes-box { background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 6px; padding: 16px 20px; margin: 16px 0 24px; }
    .scopes-box p { margin: 0 0 10px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: #111; }
    .scopes { margin: 0; line-height: 2; }
    .scope-tag { display: inline-block; background: #e8f0fe; color: #1a56db; font-size: 12px; padding: 3px 10px; border-radius: 12px; font-weight: 500; margin: 0 4px 4px 0; }
    .divider { border: none; border-top: 1px solid #e5e7eb; margin: 28px 0; }
    .footer { padding: 20px 40px; color: #9ca3af; font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.6; }
    .footer a { color: #6b7280; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="header">
      <h1>emergent memory</h1>
      <p>Knowledge graph platform</p>
    </div>
    <div class="body">

      <p>Hi there,</p>

      <p>
        <strong>{{senderName}}</strong> has granted you read-only access to the
        <strong>{{projectName}}</strong> knowledge graph on Memory.
      </p>

      <div class="what-is">
        <p>
          <strong>What is this?</strong> Memory is a knowledge graph platform that stores structured information —
          entities, relationships, documents, and decisions — about a project. With this access, your AI assistant
          (Claude, Cursor, Cloud Code, etc.) can query and search that knowledge directly, giving it context about
          <strong>{{projectName}}</strong> without you having to explain it every time.
          <br><br>
          Your access is <strong>read-only</strong>: you can search and browse, but cannot modify anything.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="scopes-box">
        <p>What you can do with this access:</p>
        <div class="scopes">
          <span class="scope-tag">Search the knowledge graph</span>
          <span class="scope-tag">Browse entities &amp; relationships</span>
          <span class="scope-tag">Read schemas</span>
          <span class="scope-tag">View agent definitions</span>
          <span class="scope-tag">Read project metadata</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="divider">

      <div class="key-box">
        <p class="label">Your API Key — keep this private</p>
        <code class="code">{{apiKey}}</code>
        <p class="warning">⚠ This key grants read-only access to <strong>{{projectName}}</strong>. Do not forward this email or share the key publicly. It will not be shown again.</p>
      </div>

      <hr class="divider">

      <div class="section">
        <h2>Connect your AI assistant</h2>
        <p class="subtitle">Add the config below to your preferred tool. The MCP server endpoint is: <code style="background:#f1f5f9;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:3px;font-size:12px;">{{mcpUrl}}</code></p>

        <div class="client">
          <h3>⚡ One-click install (Claude Desktop)</h3>
          <p class="path">Opens Claude Desktop and adds the server automatically</p>
          <a href="{{installUrl}}" style="display:inline-block;background:#1a1a2e;color:#fff;text-decoration:none;padding:10px 22px;border-radius:6px;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;margin:4px 0;">Add to Claude Desktop →</a>
        </div>

        <div class="client">
          <h3>Claude.ai (web)</h3>
          <p class="path">Settings → Connectors → Add custom connector</p>
          <ol style="margin:8px 0 10px;padding-left:20px;font-size:14px;color:#374151;line-height:1.8;">
            <li>Go to <a href="https://claude.ai/settings/connectors" style="color:#1a56db;">claude.ai/settings/connectors</a></li>
            <li>Click <strong>Add custom connector</strong></li>
            <li>Enter the MCP URL above, then open <strong>Advanced settings</strong> and add header <code style="background:#f1f5f9;padding:1px 5px;border-radius:3px;font-size:12px;">X-API-Key</code> → your API key</li>
          </ol>
          <a href="https://claude.ai/settings/connectors" style="display:inline-block;background:#d97706;color:#fff;text-decoration:none;padding:10px 22px;border-radius:6px;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;margin:4px 0;">Open Connectors Settings →</a>
        </div>

        <div class="client">
          <h3>Claude Desktop (manual)</h3>
          <p class="path">~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json &nbsp;(macOS)<br>%APPDATA%\Claude\claude_desktop_config.json &nbsp;(Windows)</p>
          <code class="code">{{snippets.claudeDesktop}}</code>
        </div>

        <div class="client">
          <h3>Claude Code (CLI)</h3>
          <p class="path">Save as <strong>.mcp.json</strong> in your project root, or run:<br>
          <code style="background:#f1f5f9;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:3px;font-size:12px;">claude mcp add memory --transport http {{mcpUrl}} -H "X-API-Key: &lt;your-key&gt;"</code></p>
          <code class="code">{{snippets.claudeCode}}</code>
        </div>

        <div class="client">
          <h3>Cursor</h3>
          <p class="path">Settings → MCP → Add server</p>
          <code class="code">{{snippets.cursor}}</code>
        </div>

        <div class="client">
          <h3>Google Cloud Code / Gemini Code Assist</h3>
          <p class="path">Save as <strong>.gemini/settings.json</strong> in your project root (or ~/.gemini/settings.json for global)</p>
          <code class="code">{{snippets.cloudCode}}</code>
        </div>

      </div>

      <hr class="divider">

      <p style="font-size:14px;color:#6b7280;">
        To revoke this access, ask <strong>{{senderName}}</strong> to delete the token from the project's API token settings.
      </p>

      <p style="font-size:14px;color:#6b7280;">
        If you weren't expecting this email, you can safely ignore it — no action is required and no account has been created for you.
      </p>

    </div>
    <div class="footer">
      <p>
        Sent by <strong>{{senderName}}</strong> via emergent memory ·
        <a href="https://emergent.memory">emergent.memory</a><br>
        MCP endpoint: <a href="{{mcpUrl}}">{{mcpUrl}}</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
